Benue State police command yesterday announced that a new Commissioner of Police has been posted to the state. He is CP. Mukaddas Muhammad Garba, who has since assumed duty.  The commandâ€™s Public Relations Officer, DSP. Anene Sewuese Catherine, in a statement said, until his posting to Benue State command, Mukaddas was a Commissioner of Police at the Office of the National Security Adviser. Anene quoted the new police commissioner as assuring the general public of his commitment to rid the state of crime in collaboration with other security agencies and with the cooperation of the good people of the state.